			<div class="content" id="post-content-4835793">
									

<p>Hey! I recently came up with an idea for a SCP Article and Concept that I don't think has ever been done before and isn't really covered in the wiki's legal guidelines.</p>
<p>Essentially I want to create a VTuber (Virtual YouTuber or Twitch Streamer) to stream on Twitch with. VTuber's are generally 3D models that are rigged to react to the operator's movements and emotions. I wanted to create one based off of a SCP article (That i am currently writing) which would be useed as his backstory.</p>
<p>For more information on the Concept: <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13894131/reality-warping-anime-husbando-vtuber-seeking-greenlight">VTuber SCP Concept</a></p>
<p>So&#8230;. I have a lot of questions&#8230;</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Questions about Twitch Licensing and Credits:<br />
1. Since the Character I would be streaming as is based on a SCP Article which falls under SCPwiki’s CC Licensing, I would assume the content I produce would need to fall under that same License? If so, I'm not sure how to set that up with twitch as I'm not entirely sure what their content falls under.</p>
<p>2. With the Character being an original creation of mine, would I still need to link to it’s article page and the Author (Me) for credit? Or would just linking to the SCPwiki be sufficient?</p>
<p>3. What rules and/or limitations (if any) would I need to abide by in my content since twitch is an Offsite platform? Examples: 1. Would I be able to stream myself as this character playing a game? even though the game may fall under a different license than CC? 2. As a musician, would I be able to cover copyrighted songs? (provided I follow twitch’s guidelines concerning music as well)</p>
<p>Questions about the Model:<br />
I created the Model and Name before I had the idea to make it a SCP. In that case, would the model (including related images) and name still belong to me, but just be used on the wiki and on stream with my permission? Or would the model and name need to be under CC as well?</p>
<p>Not all of the content being producing would be directly related to the SCP universe, but if the character is connected, I'm not sure what limitations and restrictions would be applied</p>
<p>I love the SCP Universe and don't want to do anything that would be against their guidelines, nor do I want to incur the wrath of a DMCA Take down.</p>
<p>In closing I have no idea what I am doing lol, and any legal help or advice is extremely appreciated!</p>
<p>(There are probably many things that I have not thought of and many questions may rise up. if you have any questions or suggestions of other questions I should be asking, please let me know)</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

