				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/manymeats" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2104082); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2104082&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610226564" alt="ManyMeats" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2104082)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/manymeats" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2104082); return false;" >ManyMeats</a></span> <span class="odate time_1607127020 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">05 Dec 2020 00:10</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4836445">
									

<p>First and foremost, this is my opinion as one writer to another. Although I am a member of SCPWiki staff I am not speaking to you in any way shape or form as a member of staff. This is just two people talking writing.</p>
<p>As respectfully as possible, this is a tremendous amount of labor and thought-process to undertake for something you have barely begun drafting. The types of minutia you're looking to hammer out could disappear like a puff of smoke in the wind if you fall at writing the underlying SCP.</p>
<p>While I am not a member of the licensing team and do not have any formal opinions or recommendations regarding licensing, I do have several years experiencing on the site including providing feedback and writing successful articles.</p>
<p>You're going to look and feel <em>very silly</em> if you go to all this trouble for something that is summarily deleted. Do not put the cart before the horse with dreams of a smash hit SCP and your own cult Twitch following that blooms from it.</p>
<p>Dreaming big and having ambitions are wonderful, and I hope you have a chance to stare down your goals in life and go for it one day. But dreams are also built upon the little steps along the way. You have no twitch channel if you have no article. Write it first. Make it good. Make it great. Then maybe we can talk about this.</p>
<p>If you cannot see one existing without the other, then that's all the more reason to step back and reconsider what you're doing.</p>

							</div>

								
					
